{
  "texts": [
    "This OPE is usually taken as the definition of ϵ.",
    "We can deform this action to add a background charge q via [32] C Linear dilaton systemsS = - ϵ 2π d 2 z ∂ϕ ∂ϕ + 1 4 qRϕ,where R is the Ricci scalar for the worldsheet metric.",
    "This gives a family of CFTs with stress tensorsT q (z) = ϵ 1 2 (∂ϕ) 2 - 1 2 q∂ 2 ϕ,and associated central chargec = 1 -3ϵq 2.The operator ∂ϕ is quasiprimary, with OPE T q (z)∂ϕ(w) ∼ q (z -w) 3 + ∂ϕ (z -w) 2 + ∂ 2 ϕ z -w, whist e mϕ is primary with weight h(e mϕ) = 1 2 ϵm(m + ϵq).In the absence of a background charge, ∂ϕ would generate a symmetry ϕ → ϕ + ϵα for constant α via the Noether chargeQ = dz ∂ϕ.This symmetry is now anomalous, with a non-trivial variation in the actionδS = - αq 8π d 2 z √ hR(h) = -αq(1 -g),where we have been explicit to include the volume form for the worldsheet metric.",
    "In physical correlation functions, this anomaly is cancelled by screening operators in the measure with a non-trivial transformation under Q and poles in the correlation function from inserting ∂ϕ(z).",
    "We include two examples below."
  ]
}